            <thetext>cyradm cannot currently be safely used from shell script,
because the password would have to be passed on the command line.
This patch checks if string supplied as a &quot;password&quot; on
the command line is actually a file, and uses the contents
of that file as the password instead.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
